# i18n messages

Messages merge in [`src/i18n/request.ts`](../../src/i18n/request.ts): `deepMerge(shared, locale)` — locale values override shared on the same key path.

## One key, one file

| Case                      | Where to add                                                            |
| ------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Same text in ja and en    | `shared.json` only                                                      |
| Different text per locale | **Both** `ja.json` and `en.json` (same key path) — not in `shared.json` |
| Never                     | The same leaf key in `shared.json` and a locale file                    |

Duplicate paths make shared entries dead code and confuse maintenance.

## Additive locale keys

Locale files may add keys under namespaces that exist in shared (e.g. `hero.scrollAria` next to shared `hero.scrollLabel`). **No overlapping leaf keys.**

Types in [`src/global.d.ts`](../../src/global.d.ts) use `shared & ja` — keep `ja.json` and `en.json` structurally in sync for localized keys.

## Checklist when adding text

1. Locale-agnostic or locale-specific?
2. Pick file(s): shared **or** ja + en (both).
3. Grep `src/messages/` for the key path — no duplicate paths.
4. Use the key in components via `useTranslations` / `getTranslations`.

## Out of scope for routine edits

- Do not change merge logic in `request.ts`.
- Do not localize shared English UI chrome unless the user asks.
